Grady Ward (grady@netcom.com) wrote:
[selective snips]
: The Moby Words product has a file of 160,000 phrases that
: I thought would be used to flag and eliminate cliches.  Ironically a
: customer of mine using this data to flag cliches is doing it because
: his customers want to *verify* that they are using the cliche 'correctly'(!)

: The Moby Part-of-Speech list is most frequently cited as second more useful
: to the 1,000 words sorted by frequency in doing smart OCR. If you know two
: articles rarely occur side-by-side 'Paris in the the spring' then you can
: rank the word to recognized as not likely to be an article immediately after
: you have parsed one.

